The paper proposes a deep learning framework based on a randomized neural network, which is a popular approach in the field of neural networks. The paper also discusses the use of ensemble learning, which is a common technique in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed framework on benchmark datasets from diverse domains, indicating a focus on machine learning applications, which suggests the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as likely possibilities.
